localString.value: One of several items associated with the ancient lich, robes of this sort pale in comparison to the power of the better known and unique Eye or Hand of Vecna. Still, simply being kept in his presence was enough to impart substantial magical energies.
Made from a fine silk, this robe seems to have a permanent aura of light around it.
This is your basic iron skinning knife used to skin animals.
This is a standard food ration
This is a cooked steak. You cannot tell which animal it came from.
Used as often in the peasant's home as the dungeon's dark, these simple concoctions are common throughout Faerun.
This is a tanner's sewing kit used to make bags out of leather.
With the power to staunch the flow of blood or knit a broken bone, these potions are in common use among the dangerous professions.
Alchemist's Fire is a sticky, adhesive substance that ignites on contact with air.
A flask of acid that can be thrown at enemies.
This is an oil flask. You may use it to refill a lantern, or try to light it and throw at someone
This is a standard lantern, you must refill it with oil every 6 hours of use.
This is a standard cheap disposable torch.
This is a bedroll, to use it, drop it on the ground.
This is a bedroll. You can use it by placing it on the ground.
This is a healing kit, used by those with skill, to stop the bleeding and stabilize patients.
This is the primary tool thieves use to disarm traps and pick locks
This is the primary tool thieves use to disarm traps and pick locks It seems extremely well made
This knife-like tool is used for tinkering.
Essence of Acid for making Acid Arrows and Bolts.
Essence of Cold for making Frozen Arrows and Bolts.
Essence of Electricity for making Electrical Arrows and Bolts.
Essence of Fire for making Flaming Arrows and Bolts.

The young tinkerer has many interesting devices that they can build, along with their base wires, widgets and gears. Some of these devices are even useful!
Gnomish Fire Stick - Using the drawing below, construct an enclosure for the Flaming Alchemy pack using 2 copper wires. Be certain to not build this device around an open flame.
Tinkered Mining Helmet - Protects and is functional! Using a crafted copper open helmet as a base, attach an Electrical Alchemy pack. Use 2 copper wires for controlling the device, as indicated...traditionally, the light is activated with a chin switch.
Gnomish Stun Rod - Useful for temporarily disabling brigands that you may meet on the road. Using the widget for the body of the device, carefully attach the Electrical Alchemy pack with 2 copper control wires. DO NOT POINT THE DEVICE AT YOURSELF DURING CONSTRUCTION. Doing so may lead to injury.
This is a jeweler's desk used for making jewelry.
This is a jeweler's desk used for making jewelry.
Hearty billows fan the forge-borne flames. The air is blisteringly hot, leaving you feel light-headed and not quite yourself.
This sturdy blacksmith's anvil bears the dented sheen of long use. Something in you wonders what great weapons and armor have been shaped upon its well-worn surface.

The grease covered contraption before you contains the necessary tools, clamps, cutter, vials and other assorted bits needed to use the tinkering skill. A tinkerer tool is needed to activate and use parts of the set.
